Wash and dry all produce. Dice @Roma tomato{1}(diced). Halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}(halved, peeled, and thinly sliced); mince a few slices until you have 2 TBSP (4 TBSP for 4 servings). Zest and quarter @lime{1}(zested and quartered). Halve, core, and thinly slice @long green pepper{1}(halved, cored, and thinly sliced).

In a #small bowl{}, combine tomato, minced onion, a squeeze of lime juice, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

In a separate small bowl, combine @sour cream{4%tbsp} with a squeeze of lime juice. Season with salt and pepper. Stir in @water{1%tsp} 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add green pepper; cook until lightly browned and slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add sliced onion; cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are browned and tender, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in half the @Southwest spice blend{1%tbsp} (you'll use the rest in the next step) and a splash of water. Cook, stirring, until veggies are coated and water has mostly evaporated. Season with salt and pepper. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Pat @chicken breast strips{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}. Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for veggies over medium-high heat. Add chicken and remaining Southwest spice; cook, stirring occasionally, until chicken is browned, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Stir in @Tex-Mex paste{1%bottle}, lime zest, and a squeeze of lime juice until chicken is coated and cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and pepper. Turn off heat.

Meanwhile, wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between #plates{} and fill with chicken and veggies. Top with pico de gallo, @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup}, and lime crema. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Serve chicken, veggies, pico de gallo, Monterey Jack, lime crema, and lime wedges in separate bowls or plates for a build-your-own fajita bar!